    "intitule": "Exercice 2 : Calcul de la covariance",
    "type": "ressource",
    "niveau": "medium",
    "enonce": {
      "texte": "<p>On considère la série statistique suivante :</p><table style='width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;'><tr style='background: #e3f2fd;'><th style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>$x$</th><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>2</td><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>4</td><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>6</td><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>8</td></tr><tr style='background: #f5f5f5;'><th style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>$y$</th><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>5</td><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>7</td><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>9</td><td style='padding: 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd;'>11</td></tr></table><ol><li>Calculer la covariance $\\operatorname{Cov}(x, y)$.</li><li>Calculer le coefficient de corrélation linéaire $r$.</li></ol>",
      "images": []
    },
    "questions": [
      {
        "numero": 1,
        "texte": "Calculer la covariance et le coefficient de corrélation.",
        "niveau": "medium",
        "reponse": "Voir explication",
        "sousQuestions": [
          {
            "numero": "1.a",
            "texte": "Calculer la covariance $\\operatorname{Cov}(x, y)$.",
            "niveau": "medium",
            "reponse": "$\\bar{x} = \\frac{2+4+6+8}{4} = 5$ <br/> $\\bar{y} = \\frac{5+7+9+11}{4} = 8$ <br/> $\\operatorname{Cov}(x, y) = \\frac{1}{4} \\sum_{i=1}^{4} (x_i - \\bar{x})(y_i - \\bar{y})$ <br/> $= \\frac{1}{4}[(2-5)(5-8) + (4-5)(7-8) + (6-5)(9-8) + (8-5)(11-8)]$ <br/> $= \\frac{1}{4}[(-3)(-3) + (-1)(-1) + (1)(1) + (3)(3)]$ <br/> $= \\frac{1}{4}[9 + 1 + 1 + 9] = \\frac{20}{4} = 5$."
          },
          {
            "numero": "1.b",
            "texte": "Calculer le coefficient de corrélation linéaire $r$.",
            "niveau": "medium",
            "reponse": "$V(x) = \\frac{1}{4} \\sum (x_i - \\bar{x})^2 = \\frac{1}{4}(9 + 1 + 1 + 9) = 5$ <br/> $V(y) = \\frac{1}{4} \\sum (y_i - \\bar{y})^2 = \\frac{1}{4}(9 + 1 + 1 + 9) = 5$ <br/> $r = \\frac{\\operatorname{Cov}(x, y)}{\\sqrt{V(x)} \\sqrt{V(y)}} = \\frac{5}{\\sqrt{5} \\times \\sqrt{5}} = \\frac{5}{5} = 1$."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
