          {
            "numero": "1.a",
            "texte": "Calculer le coefficient de corrélation linéaire $r$.",
            "niveau": "hard",
            "reponse": "$\\bar{x} = \\frac{35+38+40+42+45}{5} = 40$ <br/> $\\bar{y} = \\frac{140+152+160+168+180}{5} = 160$ <br/> $\\operatorname{Cov}(x, y) = \\frac{1}{5}[(-5)(-20) + (-2)(-8) + 0 + 2 \\times 8 + 5 \\times 20]$ <br/> $= \\frac{1}{5}[100 + 16 + 0 + 16 + 100] = \\frac{232}{5} = 46.4$ <br/> $V(x) = \\frac{1}{5}[25 + 4 + 0 + 4 + 25] = \\frac{58}{5} = 11.6$ <br/> $V(y) = \\frac{1}{5}[400 + 64 + 0 + 64 + 400] = \\frac{928}{5} = 185.6$ <br/> $r = \\frac{46.4}{\\sqrt{11.6} \\times \\sqrt{185.6}} = \\frac{46.4}{3.406 \\times 13.623} \\approx \\frac{46.4}{46.4} \\approx 1$."
