          {
            "numero": "1.a",
            "texte": "Calculer le coefficient de corrélation.",
            "niveau": "hard",
            "reponse": "$\\bar{x} = \\frac{5+8+10+12+15}{5} = 10$ <br/> $\\bar{y} = \\frac{100+85+70+60+45}{5} = 72$ <br/> $\\operatorname{Cov}(x, y) = \\frac{1}{5}[(-5)(28) + (-2)(13) + 0 + 2(-12) + 5(-27)]$ <br/> $= \\frac{1}{5}[-140 - 26 + 0 - 24 - 135] = \\frac{-325}{5} = -65$ <br/> $V(x) = \\frac{1}{5}[25 + 4 + 0 + 4 + 25] = 11.6$ <br/> $V(y) = \\frac{1}{5}[784 + 169 + 4 + 144 + 729] = \\frac{1830}{5} = 366$ <br/> $r = \\frac{-65}{\\sqrt{11.6} \\times \\sqrt{366}} \\approx \\frac{-65}{3.406 \\times 19.131} \\approx \\frac{-65}{65.17} \\approx -0.997$."
